        "That does not mean he is automatically KRG-friendly. A social-repair worldview can support minority dignity, but it can also favor state institutions and orderly reform over separatism or unilateral moves. Kurdistan Lens should therefore treat this book as context for how Lammy might hear Kurdish arguments, not as evidence of a policy commitment.",
        "The analytic question is whether Lammy's direct Iraq/KRG records later show the same language: trust, dignity, fairness, institutional reform, minorities, communities, and responsibility."
